The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             The City Diary
                A 20-year old girl was injured after she fell and her foot got trapped between a Metro Railway coach and the platform on Sunday evening. Riki Das of Belghoria was trying to catch a Tollygunge-bound train at Sovabazar station around 6.25pm. She slipped and her right foot was trapped in the small between the rear compartment and the platform. The guard and other passengers rescued her. Metro officials said she suffered minor cuts and was given first aid at the station.    Two trucks collided on Tallah Park bridge, connecting BT Road, early on Sunday. Both drivers were injured and rushed to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital, where one of them was discharged after first-aid. Both vehicles were impounded by officers of Chitpur police station.     Soumen Naskar, 25, was run over by a speeding private bus, plying from Diamond Harbour to Esplanade, on Diamond Harbour Road near Bishnupur, on the southern fringes, on Sunday afternoon. Naskar was taken to Vidyasagar Hospital, in Behala, where he was declared dead on arrival. Police arrested the driver and impounded the bus.     Three men were arrested on Saturday midnight from Sonarpur for selling deer skin and meat. Sudip Mondal, 37, was picked by officials of Piyali police station, near Gosaba, while selling deer meat on Saturday evening. He disclosed the names of Suraj Das, 33, and Debraj Mondal, 35, residents of Satjola, near Sonarpur. They were arrested from their Sonarpur residence with 11 deer skins.     Mohammad Samir, 14, was dashed by a milk van outside his residence on Gora Chand Road, in the Beniapukur area, on Sunday morning. He suffered multiple fractures on his right leg and was rushed to Calcutta National Medical College and Hospital. The driver of the van was arrested and the vehicle impounded.     Raja Roy was arrested in the Muchipara area on charges of assaulting a sex worker, Ganga Das, 35, who succumbed to her injuries on Sunday. Police said Roy had gone to a brothel on BB Ganguly Street, where he met Ganga. He was drunk and kicked her after an altercation over money.     A 27-year-old youth, Som Roy, was arrested from a building under construction at Rajarhat on Sunday. Police said he had fled Bongaon on June 22 after raping and killing a local girl. Som had been evading arrest by passing off as a daily labourer in the construction project.            
